Act I – The Beginning

You enter the road at dusk.

A milestone reads:
“Rome – 312 miles”

NPC: An old man sitting beside the road.

He only says:
“You’re walking away, not forward.”

When you turn back, the entrance is gone.



Act II – The Empty World

As you move forward:
Houses contain meals still warm

Letters describe people planning to leave “before he returns”

A church bell rings once every night, even though the tower is empty

You sometimes see a figure far ahead on the road.
You never catch up.
You never fall behind it.



Act III – The Truth of the Road

You discover ancient stone tablets:
“Rome was never a place.
Rome was an excuse.”

The road was built by people who believed movement meant meaning.
They walked to avoid confronting something behind them.
The road feeds on travelers who refuse to stop.



Final Act – Choice

At the end of the road:
A broken sign: ROME – 0 miles

No city
Just a mirror

You realize:
The road doesn’t lead to Rome
It leads away from yourself


Final Choice:

Turn back
The world becomes darker but real
The road collapses behind you

Keep walking
The road stretches forever
You become the distant figure another traveler sees
